\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid2495930\charrsid2495930 Diana:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5336154\charrsid5336154 I was born in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Trinidad{\*\xmlclose} \endash  er \'85 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}British West Indies{\*\xmlclose} as it was then.  My parents met and married very late \'85 er \'85
 my mother was well over 40 when I was born.  And my father was a research scientist \'85 erm \'85 worked on the transportation of bananas.  And my mother had been a teacher, and went over to teach in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Teacher{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Training{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}College{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Trinidad{\*\xmlclose}, and they met very soon after they were both there, and then they got stuck because of the War \endash  couldn\rquote t get back out of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Trinidad{\*\xmlclose} again.  And I was born in 1941 \'85
 erm \'85 and we lived in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Trinidad{\*\xmlclose} for quite a while, and then came back to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 a couple of times, on leave \endash  as one did \endash  from the colonies!  Both my \'85 my father was not at all well, he got malaria, and you were deemed to get ill if you stayed in the Tropics too long.  Apparently people \'85 people couldn\rquote t 
\'85 only certain people, of course, couldn\rquote t.  And we stayed with relatives, because it was just at the ending of the War \'85 well, the War had just ended by the time we got back, you couldn\rquote t get back until \rquote 
45, and then we stayed with my father\rquote s father and my mother\rquote s mother, and with various relatives around the country \'85 full of rationing, and incredibly cold winter in 1947.  Erm \'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid2495930\charrsid2495930 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5336154\charrsid5336154 
So without an income at that point, do you mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid2495930\charrsid2495930 Diana:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5336154\charrsid5336154 
I think my father was probably still \'85 erm \'85 employed by the Imperial College of Tropical Agriculture, and he was on leave, and then he went back to that, and my mother stayed on in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.  But they couldn\rquote t get housing, so my mother went back to primary school teaching, because housing came with \'85 with being a school teacher \endash 
 if you went where you were told to teach \'85 in the hard to teach \'85 amazing quiet little village school should be regarded as hard to \'85 hard to whatsit.  But anyway, erm \'85 so that\rquote s \'85 that\rquote s where we kind of came to rest 
\endash  in Hertfordshire.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid2495930\charrsid2495930 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5336154\charrsid5336154 In 1947, was this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid2495930\charrsid2495930 Diana:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5336154\charrsid5336154 Erm \'85
 yes, indeed.  That was, indeed, 1947.  And my father was still going out to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Trinidad{\*\xmlclose} and coming back again.  I think my mother had a serious mental breakdown, in fact.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid2495930\charrsid2495930 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5336154\charrsid5336154 How would that be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid2495930\charrsid2495930 Diana:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5336154\charrsid5336154 Erm \'85 it wasn\rquote 
t the life she was used to \'85 erm \'85 I don\rquote t mean to put her down at all, but, you know, Trinidad was a very social thing, and you had a lot of domestic help, and she ended up living with relatives who didn\rquote t particularly want her 
\endash  my father\rquote s father was extremely strict.  She had a small child to look after all on her own.  It was post-War, everything was rationed, and people didn\rquote t really welcome people who didn\rquote t \'85you know, who didn\rquote 
t have lots of local ties, which helped you get meat from the butcher, and bread from the \'85 from the farmer and so on.  And 
my father was away, so my mother was stuck with rather unenthusiastic relatives of his, in the middle of Northamptonshire or Hertfordshire, or \'85 for various periods, constantly moving house.  I don\rquote 
t think I had two birthdays in the same place until I was 11 or 12.  It\rquote s a long time ago, isn\rquote t it!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid2495930\charrsid2495930 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5336154\charrsid5336154 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid2495930\charrsid2495930 Diana:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5336154\charrsid5336154 It\rquote s a very \'85
 very \'85 very very different world.  But it was only years later when I looked back on my mother and I thought she was really quite withdrawn, that I began to think she \'85 she was withdrawn, with good \'85
 good reason.  But my mother was very middle-class, so she wouldn\rquote t have talked about things like \'85 like that.  If Daddy had to do things, Daddy had to do things, and if that involved him being away for a few years on end, so be it.
\par 
